Magicians are masters of element(al)s.  Yet they only have fire and magic based damage spells.<br>
Let firepet cast fire and magic spells, just give the mage cold-based spells! &lt;grin&gt;  (this is not a serious issue, just stating the obvious lack we masters of elements have when it comes to all the elements).<br>
<br>
Give Wizards Clarity? yeah, sure, more mana for them.  <br>
But they have this gather mana thing, they have familiars giving them mana and resists, ...<br>
Us Magicians have to wait till 58 for a mana-regen based spell. And at 62 we get the second in that line.  So do we get Clarity II to make up for it?  T-rods and Mod-rods are nice, but with the 1750 hp's we have on average and some mobs giving smell-of-blood aggro, 450 hp's and being beaten upon is not worth 300mana imho.<br>
<br>
There's also one more concern I have - Enchanters have no self-mana regen spells, at all.  <br>
Sure, they have access to unlimited Clarity / Clarity II / KEI / Tranqility and Voice of Quellious, but then, that's castable on others.  They don't have 1 self-only manaregen spell from which they too can benefit.  They need ask a Druid, a Bard or a Beastlord for more manaregen.  That, imho is unfair to them.<br>
<br>
There's still some balancing issues to go, but then there is this - should there be a balance to everything?  Should every class be as good as the other?<br>
