<br>
As a wizard, I don't support us having clarity. Of the four casters, we have the lowest self mana regen options available to us. First, Harverst gather between 171(lvl 34) - 326 (lvl 65) each cast, takes ten seconds to cast, and your stunned for a few seconds, and is castable every ten minutes.<br>
<br>
Familiars give a 1 tick mana regen starting at level 49 (the level 29 one doesn't). Manaskin at 52 gives us another 1 tick mana regen. By level 54, we are at best, having 3 tick mana regen. With the ability every ten minutes to get and additional 270 some mana. <br>
<br>
Magicians and Necros can cast and reclaim pets for more mana then it cost to cast the pet. I would say that defies the laws of commonsene. But it's magic. You also get self only HP and Mana regening shields in your 50's. Enchanters have clarity. Any wizard will tell you, higher mana regen rate is better then instant mana. They can cast thier clarity on themselves. Those aren't just others only spells. So enchanters have built in higher mana regen once they start getting thier clarity spells. <br>
<br>
Mana regen from top to low is Enchanters, magicians/necros, wizards. However, wizards are the most mana dependant class of the four. Why? Well, the other three get some form of pet, or the ability to charm. This allows them to safely sit and med while the pet/charmed mob does some of the work. More butt time = more mana. <br>
<br>
Wizards can only nuke. We don't have the luxury of a pet buffer if we get low. We don't have the luxury of a 90 second mezz if the pet dies like enchanters do. To sit on our but. We have a root that gets gives the mob a chance to resist every tick. So we never know when the root is going to break. It's really not the same as having a pet or the ability to mezz or charm.<br>
<br>
However, I don't advocate wizards getting clarity spells. We could use some improvements to our self only mana regen spells, but they shouldn't be better then everyone elses. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A> at: 6/16/03 11:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xreynnx>x Reynn x</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 848<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/16/03 9:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=63>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A serious concern</span><hr size=1> This pet SUCKS!<br>
